#: src-en/data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append:475
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append$//event[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_CRUISER_WIN_FORGE\"]/choice[@req=\"FR_COMMONWEALTHS_BODY\"]/text"
msgstr "(Commonwealth's Body) Attempt to repair the corpse."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append:477
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append$//event[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_CRUISER_WIN_FORGE\"]/choice[@req=\"FR_COMMONWEALTHS_BODY\"]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"The damaged factory struggles to scan the crew. Eventually, it appears to bring it back to life... but only for a moment before the forge's internal software crashes. Whatever is needed to repair the corpse is beyond the factory's repair capabilities.\n"
"\n"
"\t\t\tStrangely, the Commonwealth's brief resurrection seemed to have triggered a reaction. A strange anomaly appears on your sensors with the same energy signatures as the brief pulse you noticed the Commonwealth give off just before it shut down. Perhaps the source of the anomaly could contain the answer to bringing the body back to life permanently?"

#: src-en/data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append:486
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append$//event[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_CRUISER_WIN_FORGE\"]/choice[@req=\"FR_REQUIREMENT_MANDER_BROKEN_DEVICE\"]/text"
msgstr ""
"(Mender Drone) The device seems broken; our Mender drone should be able to "
"fix it."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append:488
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append$//event[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_CRUISER_WIN_FORGE\"]/choice[@req=\"FR_REQUIREMENT_MANDER_BROKEN_DEVICE\"]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"It takes a long time to repair the heavily damaged device, but eventually "
"your Mender is able to fully reconstruct it. Upon activation, you receive a "
"strange signal from a point in the sector where your sensors just identified"
" a massive energy spike. Whatever is there must be important."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append:497
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append$//event[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_CRUISER_WIN_FORGE\"]/choice[@req=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_PORTAL_OPENED_AND_NO_DAISY\"]/text"
msgstr "The device doesn't seem broken; try activating it."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append:499
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append$//event[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_CRUISER_WIN_FORGE\"]/choice[@req=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_PORTAL_OPENED_AND_NO_DAISY\"]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"You touch the device and it suddenly springs to life. As it activates, you "
"receive a strange signal from a point in the sector where your sensors just "
"identified a massive energy spike. Whatever is there must be important."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append:507
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append$//event[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_CRUISER_WIN_FORGE\"]/choice[@req=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_PORTAL_OPENED_AND_DAISY\"]/text"
msgstr "The device doesn't seem broken; try activating it."

#: src-en/data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append:509
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append$//event[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_CRUISER_WIN_FORGE\"]/choice[@req=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_PORTAL_OPENED_AND_DAISY\"]/event/text"
msgstr ""
"You touch the device and suddenly it springs to life. Upon activation, you receive a strange signal from a point in the sector where your sensors just identified a massive energy spike. Whatever is there must be important.\n"
"\n"
"\t\t\t\tThe device also triggers the nearby deactivated Obelisk to restore its systems! It comes back to life fully this time, although it seems to take a little while before it recovers from its stupor. It scans the room, immediately launching into a monologue upon noticing you.\n"
"\t\t\t\n"
"\t\t\t\t\"Oh gosh! Who are you? WHAT are you? You look so...strange and fleshy; are you a native to the lesser empires, perhaps? No matter, my proto-waystone has already debriefed me on the events of the past few days. You wish to visit the refuge, right? Well, far be it from me to stop another missguided soul into breaching that hellish place, but I suppouse the least I can do is tag along for the ride. Who knows, maybe I can convince someone there to actually leave their isolated little gardens.\"\n"
"\t\t\t\n"
"\t\t\t\tShe turns to you before heading inside your ship. \"Oh, I forgot to introduce myself. My name is Bellrennis, but you can call my Daisy. Now, let's get going!\""

#: src-en/data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append:518
msgid ""
"data/events_sector_obelisk.xml.append$//event[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_CRUISER_WIN_FORGE\"]/choice[@req=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_PORTAL_OPENED_AND_DAISY\"]/event/crewMember"
msgstr "Daisy"
